President Obama and German Chancellor Angela Merkel had a conversation where they discussed various topics including the ongoing peace efforts in the Middle East. Chancellor Merkel provided an update on her involvement in supporting the President's initiatives in the region. Both leaders expressed their support for the direct talks between Israel and the Palestinians and emphasized the importance of all sides making efforts to sustain the negotiations. They agreed that Israel should extend its moratorium on settlement activity and that the talks should continue until completed. The President and Chancellor Merkel also discussed Afghanistan and agreed to consult further on global issues.